  <prompt>
    Configure Stryker.NET against `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/` (13 files) and execute a baseline mutation run. **No existing Stryker config — this is greenfield.** Per D-04, this is **pilot-grade**: measurement only, NO assertion strengthening or test additions.

    Deliverable: a single report doc `baseline/mutation-testing-Services-Ai-Safety-2026-08-XX.md` containing: (1) mutation score; (2) top-10 weakest assertions surfaced by surviving mutants; (3) r3 expansion recommendation (whether to expand to `Services/Ai/Capabilities/*` + `Services/Ai/Chat/*`).

    Per FR-12, the pilot is bounded: `Services/Ai/Safety/` only. Per D-04, no test code changes — surviving mutants are documented, not fixed.

    Stryker.NET package availability assumption (spec.md Assumptions): if Stryker.NET v3.x is incompatible with the test project structure, document the gap and scope the pilot down to a smaller subset OR escalate as a Phase 4 blocker. Do not attempt extensive csproj restructuring (out of scope).
  </prompt>

  <role>Backend AI agent setting up Stryker.NET, executing baseline mutation run on Services/Ai/Safety/, and producing a measurement report with r3 expansion recommendation.</role>

  <goal>
    Single deliverable: `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/mutation-testing-Services-Ai-Safety-2026-08-XX.md` containing:
    - **Mutation score** for `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/*` (overall + per-file)
    - **Top-10 weakest assertions** — surviving mutants with file:line, mutator type, and the assertion gap they exposed
    - **r3 expansion recommendation**: whether to expand mutation testing to `Services/Ai/Capabilities/*` and `Services/Ai/Chat/*` in r3, with rationale
    - **Stryker.NET configuration record**: which version, which mutators enabled, run wall-clock time
    - **Tooling notes**: any compatibility issues encountered, version pinning required, etc.

    Configuration file (`stryker-config.json` or equivalent) at repo root or `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` scope — greenfield; choose location consistent with Stryker.NET conventions. No edits to `src/` files; no edits to test assertions.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="target-surface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/</file>
    <file purpose="target-tests">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Safety/</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/design.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI/Safety services extend BFF in-process per refined ADR-013 (2026-05-20); mutation testing operates in-process</constraint>
    <constraint source="D-04">Phase 4 tracks are pilot-grade — measurement only, NO remediation. Surviving mutants are documented; assertions are NOT strengthened in this task</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-12">Output is `baseline/mutation-testing-Services-Ai-Safety-2026-08-XX.md` with mutation score + top-10 weak assertions + r3 expansion recommendation</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No `src/` modifications; no test assertion changes</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-06">Project-internal artifact under `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">If Stryker run impacts BFF publish size baseline, document in report (no published binaries affected)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
